   2:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * 
   3:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * LICENSE INFO:
   4:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
   5:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * This is documentation for Adafruit's SSD1306 library for monochrome
   6:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * OLED displays: http://www.adafruit.com/category/63_98
   7:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
   8:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * These displays use I2C or SPI to communicate. I2C requires 2 pins
   9:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * (SCL+SDA) and optionally a RESET pin. SPI requires 4 pins (MOSI, SCK,
  10:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * select, data/command) and optionally a reset pin. Hardware SPI or
  11:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * 'bitbang' software SPI are both supported.
  12:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
  13:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * Adafruit invests time and resources providing this open source code,
  14:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * please support Adafruit and open-source hardware by purchasing
  15:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * products from Adafruit!
  16:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
  17:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * @section dependencies Dependencies
  18:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
  19:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * This library depends on <a
  20:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * href="https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit-GFX-Library"> Adafruit_GFX</a>
  21:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * being present on your system. Please make sure you have installed the latest
  22:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * version before using this library.
  23:ssd1306_driver.c ****  *
  24:ssd1306_driver.c ****  * @section author Author
